The expert: Dr. Julian Leibowitz, a professor of microbial pathogenesis and immunology at Texas A&M’s College of Medicine, stated that there is no data to directly support the claim that COVID-19 was in the US in November 2019.
Dr: Benjamin Neuman, an expert in coronaviruses and chair of the Biological Sciences department at Texas A&M University-Texarkana, also disagreed with the claim, stating that the first US case of COVID-19 was not in November 2019 but possibly earlier in January.
The World Health Organization: WHO) states that the novel coronavirus and the disease it causes were unknown before the outbreak in Wuhan, China, in December 2019.
The Centers for Disease Control and Prev: CDC) lists the earliest date of illness onset for COVID-19 in the United States as January 14, 2020.
